{
  "stem": "19895.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 213.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I ate kosher at home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in my life outside of home, I was like anybody else.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I remember father as a very observant Jew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Every single day of his life, he was putting on the, the [? fill-in, ?] which is the [INAUDIBLE] as it's known in English and, and putting on his tallits for praying.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I recall him as somebody whose belief in God and his strengths through that has had a lot of influence on me as a growing child.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I would see that maybe in many ways helped my hopes and my, my survivor, survival in the concentration camp times, because his religious belief that God is with us gave a very mystical, strong strength to me.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had beautiful holidays, even so if-- even so if going to the synagogue was not necessarily the, the most beautiful walk.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because towards the years at age 14 to 16, before the Jews were even further restricted in Hungary, carrying our prayer book to the synagogue and carrying our, our prayer shawl, my father was hiding it in a brown bag that people on the street wouldn't know that there goes a Jew to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because atrocities on streets and remarks about that were frequent.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And oftentime, I, I was proudly wearing my high school cap which had a little emblem on the front.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was very proud of that little emblem.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So was every other high school student of-- not member of the Jewish high school-- the different high schools.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "On the other hand, that was a dead giveaway that I was Jewish and I belonged to a Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
